    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; the single ASTM F1717 compression-bending condition is the primary regulatory test and the most clinically relevant loading mode for this device class. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance criteria (percent difference <10%, E/uval <1.96) across both validation laboratories. The overall credibility of the FEA model is sufficient to support the Medium model risk, Medium decision consequence context of use. Decision: Accepted with documented gap in test condition coverage.",
